      section#dc-spending.col.s12
        h4 Spending Dragon Coins
        table.responsive-table.z-depth-1
          thead
            tr
              th Item
              th Location
              th Cost
              th.center-align Priority
              th Reasoning
          tbody
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Daily Nest Reset
              td Nest
              td 50DC/day
              td.center-align.green-text Must do
              td Nests are the primary way to earn materials for obtaining gear. Materials are gated by the runs you do, so it is necessary to reset the dungeon.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Dark Boundary Entry Token (weekly limited)
              td DC market
              td 100 DC for 10
              td.center-align.green-text Must get
              td After level 35 you want to spam Dark Boundary for Dragonware. At an amazing 75% off, you must be kidding me if you tell me you aren't getting this.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Cerberus Nest Entry Ticket (Daily Limit)
              td DC Market
              td 60 DC for 2
              td.center-align.green-text Must get
              td These are basically free Cerberus Nest Runs you can do every day to sell to the bazaar. Do Cerberus Hard and at the bare minimum you get 6 DC profit. Also, if you are lucky enough to get that gold chest, congrats you got yourself a huge chunk of free dragon coins.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Buying out Manticore items for Upgrading
              td Bazaar
              td Varies
              td.center-align.orange-text Medium
              td Upgrading Manticore equipment with Manticore items has been underrated. While the upgrade is not permanent (it will not transfer to the next tier), it gives stats equal to 2 or 3 enhances, for a lower cost. As such, if you are chasing BP for the level 40 content and for harder cerberus hell modes, it is a good option. Of course, this is not a priority if you don't wish to rush to the top as F2P; you can always wait for the materials themselves to lower in price, and buying Agates remain one of the more consistent and permanent ways of upgrading your character.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Abyss Dungeon Reset
              td Abyss Dungeon
              td (20 + 30) DC/day
              td.center-align.orange-text Medium
              td Abyss nets you a good amount of experience rate and materials for Nest equipment. However, it is not as efficient as doing 20 DC stamina resets, as such it is put lower in the priority list. Of course, still reset only once if you want to get materials.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Green Agate (weekly limited)
              td DC market
              td 240DC for 40
              td.center-align.green-text High
              td Most people underestimate the amount of BP obtained from enhancements. At a low 6 DC for the first 40, it is one of the higher priority items.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Green Agate (unlimited)
              td DC market
              td 10 DC each
              td.center-align.orange-text Medium
              td After getting the 40 cheaper Agates, it is not as efficient to buy the 10 DC ones. Get it if you have handful of DC in hand.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Green Crystal (weekly limited)
              td DC market
              td 144 DC for 6
              td.center-align.green-text High
              td Try to buy this every week till you have enough to surpass all your gear to 21. At a 40% off it is a very good deal.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Green Crystal (unlimited)
              td DC market
              td 40 DC each
              td.center-align.orange-text Low-Medium
              td Not very efficient without the 40% off.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Blue Agate (weekly limited)
              td DC market
              td 21 DC each
              td.center-align.blue-text Medium-High
              td Good to get if you want to rush to 30. Not very efficient otherwise (getting Green Agate to convert is still priority if you haven't bought it yet).
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Big Dark Boundary Pack (weekly limited)
              td DC market
              td 1600 for 8 (40 total runs)
              td.center-align.orange-text Medium
              td This pack is honestly a little expensive, so it isn't very high priority, but do get this if you want to farm more dragonwares.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Unlocking third attributes
              td Rare Heraldries
              td 120 DC at level 35
              td.center-align.red-text Low
              td Honestly, it is okay to not use 3 stat rare heraldries as we aren't at a high level yet.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Buying plates/heraldries
              td Bazaar
              td Varies
              td.center-align.orange-text Medium
              td Again, not very necessary unless you want to have a very high BP. If it is quite affordable do go for it.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Stamina Refresh
              td Stamina Bar
              td 20 DC for first few
              td.center-align.orange-text Medium
              td This is a must get if you are nearing Level 32 (to hit the level seal faster), or trying to rush content. Avoid using more than 20 dc for refreshes as we have lunch and dinner rewards. Also get this if you need it for daily/weekly rewards.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Gold Chest
              td Benefit Tab
              td 10 DC for 1
              td.center-align.purple-text Only for Daily
              td This is only really bought if you need extra points to complete your daily/weekly rewards.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Pandora's Seed (weekly limited)
              td DC market
              td 40 each (400 for 10)
              td.center-align.red-text Low
              td It is a very high chance of getting items that are lower than 40 DC, so only buy them with disposable income.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Battle/Palace Medals
              td Bazaar Auction (Guild and World)
              td Varies
              td.center-align.orange-text Medium
              td Moniker is a decent stat boost. I recommend getting medals if they look affordable.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Farm
              td Home
              td 500 DC for a plot
              td.center-align.red-text Very Low
              td Only viable for pay players as stealing crops from friends are more practical
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Rare Fairy Eggs
              td Fairy
              td 1980DC for 10
              td.center-align.red-text Low
              td You get enough A rank fairies from daily eggs and events.
            tr
              td
                label
                  input(type="checkbox")
                  span Guild Sign In
              td Guild
              td 100 DC for 2000 Contri
              td.center-align.green-text Medium-High
              td Guild sign-ins are an underestimated way of obtaining Battle Medals faster. Typically if world boss medals stay low it isn't very high priority, but as people are beginning to snipe medals away, it becomes apparent to use contribution to buy battle medals as frequently as you can. After Moniker V Guild Sign In is less efficient however.
